Options:
1. Add a break condition
2. Add a return statement
3. If intentional, add a comment

Example:
```
while (true) {
data = getData();
if (data == null) {
break; // Exit condition
}
process(data);
}
```

Extract loop body to a separate component:

```jsx
// ❌ Wrong
items.map(item => {
const [value, setValue] = useSettings(item.initial); // Violation!
return <Item value={value} />;
});

// ✅ Correct: Create a component for each item
function ItemWrapper({ item }) {
const [value, setValue] = useSettings(item.initial);
return <Item value={value} />;
}

items.map(item => <ItemWrapper key={item.id} item={item} />);
```

